---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: 'Are the calculations on this site certified engineering designs?',
    answer: 'No. All calculators provide preliminary educational estimates only. They do not constitute certified engineering plans, safety documentation, or compliance designs. Always verify with a licensed professional.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I use these tools for commercial projects?',
    answer: 'You may use the output as a starting reference, but all results must be independently verified by qualified engineers before use in any commercial, industrial, or safety-critical application.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does Battery Calculators store my calculation inputs?',
    answer: 'No. All calculations run entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. No inputs, results, or personal data are transmitted to or stored on any server.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Who owns the content and formulas on this site?',
    answer: 'The formulas, text, and code on Battery Calculators are owned by the site operator. You may reference and learn from them, but reproduction for competing purposes is not permitted without written consent.',
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Battery Calculators"
  description="Terms of Service for Battery Calculators. Read about educational use, accuracy of calculations, and limitation of liability."
  canonical="https://batterycalculators.com/terms"
  schema="faqPage"
  schemaName="Battery Calculators Terms of Service"
  schemaDescription="Terms of Service for BatteryCalculators.com battery calculators."
  schemaUrl="https://batterycalculators.com/terms"
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Terms of Service' }]} />

    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
      <span class="text-label-uppercase text-m-blue-light text-xs block mb-4">LEGAL TERMS</span>
      <h1 class="text-display-md text-primary mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light">
        Effective date: June 9, 2026.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-body-md text-body font-light">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using Battery Calculators, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, please discontinue use of the website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">2. Educational Purpose</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Battery Calculators is an independent, publicly accessible platform built for educational and preliminary engineering reference. All calculators, formulas, worked examples, and guides are provided to help users understand battery sizing concepts, electrical calculations, and energy storage fundamentals.
        </p>
        <p>
          The tools are not intended to replace professional engineering judgment, certified design processes, or compliance documentation required by local codes and standards.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">3. No Professional Engineering Advice</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Nothing on this website constitutes professional engineering advice, consultation, or a client-engineer relationship. The calculators produce estimates based on idealized mathematical models and publicly available reference formulas.
        </p>
        <p>
          For any project involving physical installation, electrical wiring, fire safety, structural mounting, or regulatory compliance, you must consult a licensed engineer and reference applicable standards such as NEC, NFPA 855, IEEE 1547, ISO 13297, or local building codes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">4. Accuracy of Calculations</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We strive for transparency and accuracy. Every calculator exposes the exact mathematical formulas used, along with worked examples, so you can verify results independently.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          However, calculations are based on simplified assumptions including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-body-sm text-muted mb-4">
          <li>Constant wire resistivity without contact resistance.</li>
          <li>Linear temperature derating models.</li>
          <li>Idealized inverter efficiency curves.</li>
          <li>Standard calendar ageing without site-specific environmental factors.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Real-world results will vary. You are responsible for validating all outputs before making design or purchasing decisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Battery Calculators and its operator accept no liability for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use or misuse of this website, its calculators, or its content.
        </p>
        <p>
          This includes, but is not limited to, system failures, property damage, personal injury, fire, electrocution, financial losses, or any other harm resulting from reliance on the calculator outputs without independent professional verification.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          All content on this website — including text, formulas, calculator logic, code, layout, and design — is the intellectual property of Battery Calculators unless otherwise stated.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may reference, learn from, and share links to individual pages for non-commercial educational purposes. Reproduction of content for competing platforms or commercial redistribution requires written permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">7. External Links</h2>
        <p>
          This website may contain links to external resources for reference purposes. Battery Calculators does not control, endorse, or assume responsibility for the content, accuracy, or practices of third-party websites.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@batterycalculators.com" class="text-primary hover:text-m-blue-light transition-colors underline underline-offset-4">contact@batterycalculators.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <FAQSection items={faqItems} />
  </div>
</Layout>
